oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Bovine Blood Glucose Concentrations: Point of Care Testing with Glucometers
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Landa, C.
Swecker, W. S.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: blood glucose
disease
hand-held glucometers
field measurement
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Blood glucose concentrations are commonly utilized to evaluate both metabolic and disease status of animals. The objective of this study was to compare the accuracy of two hand-held glucometers for field measurement of glucose in cattle.
